<HEADLINE>
FT  06 JAN 94 / World News in Brief: Brian Johnston, voice of cricket, dies
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The prime minister and leading cricketers paid tribute to commentator Brian
Johnston, who died at the age of 81. Mr Johnston, known as 'Johnners' and
the BBC's voice of cricket, recently suffered a heart attack. His
conversational commentaries for BBC Radio's Test Match Special enabled him
to establish a special rapport with his audience. John Major said his death
meant summers would not be the same again.
