   By RICHARD WATERS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
J. P. Morgan sold its US corporate trust business in the latest sign of
consolidation in the fiercely competitive US market for custody and other
securities services, writes Richard Waters. Morgan business, which acts as
trustee to 3,800 bond issues for 650 US companies, has been bought by First
Bank System, a Minneapolis-based banking group. First Bank said this and
other acquisitions would make its corporate trustee business the fifth
largest in the US.
