Zantac, the world's best selling drug. At stake is a slice of a market that
is worth Dollars 1.9bn (Pounds 1.3bn) a year to Glaxo in the US alone.
Glaxo's move is a response to a new challenge to Zantac's patents by
Genpharm in the wake of a court ruling in favour of Glaxo in September 1993.
Genpharm is now challenging two of Glaxo's US patents on the drug.
