<HEADLINE>
FT  05 JAN 94 / Record sales for mobile phone groups
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The UK's two leading mobile telephone operators reported more than 120,000
net new connections in December, easily the highest monthly total since the
launch of cellular networks in the mid-1980s.
Vodafone, the largest operator, reported a net increase of 52,500 in
December, taking its total to more than 1m.
Cellnet, a joint venture between British Telecommunications and Securicor,
reported a net increase of 68,700, taking its total to 906,000. Cellnet
added more connections in December than during the whole of 1992.
Vodafone and Cellnet together made a net addition of nearly 750,000 new
subscribers during last year, taking the total number of UK cellular
subscribers, including Mercury One-2-One, the third network, to nearly 2m.
Cellnet yesterday launched a digital cellular network operating to the
pan-European GSM standard (global system for mobile communications). It
competes with a similar service started by Vodafone last autumn.
</TEXT>
