FT  05 JAN 94 / Prisons on alert as system shows strains
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOSEPH MANN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Security was increased at prisons across Venezuela yesterday after a riot
and mass breakout at two separate institutions left more than 100 prisoners
dead, writes Joseph Mann. Soldiers and firemen were still pulling bodies out
of a compound in Maracaibo, Venezuela's second-largest city, after about 100
prisoners died during a riot and fire on Monday.
Venezuelan authorities said that two rival bands of prisoners began fighting
late on Monday afternoon and set fire to prison buildings. Units of the
National Guard were called in to crush the ensuing riot.
Meanwhile, 40 prisoners escaped and nine were killed while trying to flee
Tocoron prison, 75 miles south-west of Caracas, while government officials
were dealing with the aftermath of the Maracaibo rampage early on Tuesday
morning. A National Guardsman also died.
</TEXT>
