<DATELINE>
   BEIJING
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
A Chinese city and a Russian one have agreed to build a cross-border free
economic and trade zone, Reuter reports from Beijing. In the first such
venture between the two countries, Heihe in China's northeastern province of
Heilongjiang and its neighbour Blagoveshchensk in the Russian Far East will
set up the zone from either end of a pontoon bridge to be built over the
river separating them.
