<HEADLINE>
FT  04 JAN 94 / Pay freeze at Alitalia
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By REUTER
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   ROME
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Alitalia, the Italian state airline, yesterday froze the wages of its flying
crew pending agreement with unions on a plan to drive the loss-making group
back into the black, company officials said, Reuter reports from Rome.
Pilots, flight technicians and cabin crew will only recieve pay rises when
the rescue plan has been settled.
</TEXT>
